<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="634" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,760,635,1490]" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,699,722]" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body slightly oval, length 
<quantity box="[554,685,699,722]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="634" unit="mm" value="4.75" valueMax="5.8" valueMin="3.7">3.7–5.8 mm</quantity>
. Elytra and pronotum lacking erect setae, head about as long as pronotum. Eyes large, oval, clearly visible in dorsal view, situated at base of rostrum. Rostrum lacking carinae, densely punctate, scrobes visible dorsally. Antennae (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[151,182,1976,1995]" captionTargetBox="[159,760,1194,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-812@4.[151,761,1193,1960]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Anchonidium caucasicum Motschulsky, 1845: a – antenna; b – abdominal ventrites I–V; c – spermatheca; d – sternite VIII. Anchonidium perpensum Faust, 1886: e – spermatheca; f – sternite VIII. Aparopion costatum (Fåhraeus, 1843): g – antenna. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177898/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[151,179,859,882]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="634" unit="g" value="4.0">4g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) slender, scape long, reaching anterior margin of eyes, funicule with 7 antennomeres, antennomeres II and III approx. of same length, all antennomeres elongate. Pronotum lacking carinae or smooth median line, rugosely punctate, constricted before apex, postocular lobe absent, scutellum not visible. Elytra wide, EL/EW ratio &lt;1.25, interstriae elevated, granulate, striae composed of single row of small deep punctures, apex of each elytron with well-defined preapical constriction. Procoxae separated, mesocoxae widely separated, ventrite I and II separated by straight suture, ventrite I clearly longer than II. Tarsomere III strongly bilobed, onychium long, at least as long as tarsomeres II and III together. Median lobe of aedeagus asymmetrical, with internal sclerites, parameres absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="634" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,760,635,1490]" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1307,1330]" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus was recently revised (Zඎඉඉൺ &amp; Oඌൾඅඅൺ 1999) and four species were recognized, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Jacquelin du Val, 1855)" baseAuthorityName="Jacquelin du Val" baseAuthorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Aparopion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="634" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chevrolati">
<emphasis box="[673,689,1339,1362]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">chevrolati</emphasis>
(Jacquelin du Val, 1855)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Reitter, 1891" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Aparopion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="634" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suturidens">
<emphasis box="[533,674,1371,1394]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">A. suturidens</emphasis>
Reitter, 1891
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[272,345,1403,1426]" name="France" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">France</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[398,448,1403,1426]" name="Italy" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">Italy</collectingCountry>
, the newly described species 
<taxonomicName authority="Zuppa &amp; Osella, 1999" authorityName="Zuppa &amp; Osella" authorityYear="1999" box="[151,556,1435,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Aparopion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="634" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="numidicum">
<emphasis box="[151,302,1435,1458]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">A. numidicum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="ZUPPA A. M. &amp; OSELLA G." box="[311,556,1435,1458]" pageId="5" pageNumber="634" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref10308" refString="ZUPPA A. M. &amp; OSELLA G. 1999: Revisione del genere Aparopion Hampe, 1861 (Coleoptera, Curculionidae, Molytinae). Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, Botanica Zoologia 23: 1 - 49." type="journal article" year="1999">Zuppa &amp; Osella, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[625,708,1435,1458]" name="Algeria" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, and relatively widespread 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampe" authorityYear="1861" box="[387,512,1467,1490]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Aparopion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="634" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costatum">
<emphasis box="[387,512,1467,1490]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="634">A. costatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
